<font style="display: none;"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=retrotorque>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/18/02 8:16:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4550.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/solidnate/vsig.gif height=106 width=106></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which improves skill more?</span><hr size=1> Both are important. Sketching is good for eperimenting and learning techniques. Sketching gives you experience with subjects. Finishing is taking the sketch and refining it into a finished picture. The only way you'll learn to interperate sketches is by finishing them. <br>
<br>
Study all sorts of subjects too. Just drawing people all the time will come back to bite you when you want or need to draw something else.<br>
<br>
Another note, never be shy of using reference material and drawing from life when you sketch. You won't learn much by drawing things only from your head. <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chikin>Chikin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/20/02 2:26:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4550.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://homepage.ntlworld.com/spoonofdoom/dogtopus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Which improves skill more?</span><hr size=1> Don't forget critiquing. ;)<br>
